<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: And have you, Sir, made any contribution besides criticize and criticize?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?dylan waite">dylan waite</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:14 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: And have you, Sir, made any contribution besides criticize and criticize?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=735" TARGET=_self>Re: And have you, Sir, made any contribution besides criticize and criticize?</A> (Min)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Yes you write a master's thesis on the inherent problems, but

<BR>&gt; you didn't write anything on how you could improve it, which is
<BR>&gt; basicly what we are on this board for.
<P>i argue that the solution is NOT more open PK like everyone seems to want but, actually, more newbie saving restrictions....Verant will never take rampant UO-style PvP seriously
<P>&gt; Personally I skipped almost all of Rand/Whitewolf and the Cobra
<BR>&gt; Sin guy's flames toward each other, and I don't really think the
<BR>&gt; conversation flow have really been disrupted, most of the people
<BR>&gt; skipped their flames too.
<P>maybe my vision is skewed here as i seem to have been sucked right into the middle of it...but i DO notice an inordinate amount of flaming going on here...i'm surprised people haven't started e-mail bombing each other yet
<P>&gt; Myaybe but he is still the EQ PvP GM, and he is open to ideas at
<BR>&gt; least, I have see no evidence that he prefers ex-UOers'
<BR>&gt; suggestions and shoot down others, if you have good suggestion
<BR>&gt; he will listen, just post it.
<P>i didn't say he preferred UO refugees......i only said i don't know where he stands...on ANYTHING
<P>&gt; Did you read the first post in that thread? I specificly asked
<BR>&gt; if whether this topic should even be discussed, Geiger said yes,
<BR>&gt; so do you know more about what the programmers in Verant are
<BR>&gt; doing than Geiger does?
<P>i'm afraid i missed that....given everything i heard during beta i have a hard time believing Verant is considering doing away with the level/skill system....i think you likely misunderstood geiger here, or he misunderstood your question
<P>&gt; That would depend on what kind of PvP style you play, I have
<BR>&gt; played 4 years on a MUD that HAS PK SWITCH, and let me tell you
<BR>&gt; the atmosphere on that Mud between PK and non-PK is very
<BR>&gt; friendly, pk switch suits me perfectly fine and that is why I
<BR>&gt; have high hopes for EQ. Tell me, have you ever played in a MUD
<BR>&gt; that has the pk switch feature?
<P>honestly, i have not ......my problem is not going to be with the +PvP people on the normal servers, my problem is with the +PvP server which the players seem to want to turn in the apocolyptic battle at the end of time.....very few people, i think, want this but it only takes a few rampant pk's to bring the general populace down to their level....the situation will erode until we do, really, have EverQuake....this is my worst nightmare an i don't want to see it happen....my advice is to (since banning them is a bit draconian) cripple the ability of the k3wLd00d to be disruptive....not less rstriction on PvP, MORE.......then maybe Verant's vision of legitimate PvP can be realized
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
